# Building on Existing Classes

**Inheritance** lets you create a new class that **inherits** all attributes and methods from an existing class:

```
class Animal:          # Parent/Base class
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name
    def speak(self):
        print("...")

class Dog(Animal):     # Child/Derived class
    def speak(self):
        print(f"{self.name} says Woof!")

class Cat(Animal):
    def speak(self):
        print(f"{self.name} says Meow!")
```

Dog and Cat **inherit** `name` from Animal but **override** `speak()` with their own version!

